  <body>
    <section name="Save document type">
      <span class="shortdesc">How to save a document type.</span>

   <script type="text/javascript">
    leftpx=450;
    bottompx=350;
   </script>
   <div class='group'> 
    <div id='screenshot'><div>
     <img src="../../../../images/screenshots/cms_M13/contribs/save_document.png" alt='save document type screenshot'/> 
    </div></div>
    <p>
     The buttons for saving a documenttype are the same as for
       <a href='../../contributors/howto/save_document.html'>saving a normal document</a>.
     Note that after saving, the documenttype will NOT yet be available to write documents of that type.
    </p>
   </div>

   <p>
    The effect of saving a documenttype will not be the same as for a normal document,
    as there will be no preview of a documenttype on any site.
    After saving, <a href='./update_all_content.html'>update all content</a>
    to make the documenttype available to
    <a href='../../contributors/concepts/contributor.html'>authors</a>, to write
    documents of that type.
   </p>

